From e173ea4ce6d2b1c7885bffc856049ef0ed71377a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Evelyn Tsai <evelyn.tsai@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 19:45:34 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 04/10] mtk: mt76: mt7996: remove PPDU TxS to improve stability
 issue

Driver dependency changes
1. Refactor TX statistics to accommodate the disabling of PPDU TxS.

Switch TX MPDU statistical source from PPDU TXS to FW.

In WFDMA, TX-Free-Done events and PPDU TXS use the same ring.
Because WFDMA resource is more limited in Griffin, if too many events and TXS occupy the ring at the same time,
TX-Free-Done events may be corrupted, eventually causing serious errors, like token leakage and FW command timeout.

Hence, PPDU TXS needs to be disabled.
Consequently, TX MPDU statistical source needs to be switched from PPDU TXS to FW.

2. Add BA recovery mechanism

Send a mcu commnad to FW to enable AUTO BA mechanism.
FW will notify host to establish BA session when station is using HW
path but BA session is not established.
For mt7992/mt7996, receive event through EXT_CMD.
For mt7990, receive event through SDO event.

3. Update agg session time when receiving txfree

